headline: Why DraftKings (DKNG) Shares Are Sliding Today
summary: Shares of fantasy sports and betting company DraftKings (NASDAQ:DKNG) fell 1.9% in the afternoon session after reports revealed Crypto.com and Underdog Sports are partnering to launch sports prediction markets in the U.S., signaling increased competition in the sector. The news sent shares of other European betting and gambling companies, including Entain and Evolution, lower as well. According to a CNBC report, the new platform from Crypto.com and Underdog Sports will initially target 16 states

headline: How PayPal & other fintech firms are taking share from big banks
summary: Banking isn't what it used to be. Big banks are facing competition from the likes of PayPal (PYPL), Robinhood (HOOD), and Rocket (RKT). Great Hill Capital chairman and managing member Thomas Hayes explains why he likes PayPal specifically, while Hennessy Funds portfolio manager David Ellison shares how rising fintech firms have managed to steal the momentum.
